 Please let me know if you manage to create a working CSS-only version!


 Slow-mo Any Animation (with JS)


 Lastly, I‚Äôd like to share a solution that works for (almost) any animation, even with multiple complicated @keyframes:



 CodePen Embed Fallback



 Basically, you need to add an animation progress tracker, then carefully compute animation-delay for the new animation. However, sometimes it could be tricky (but possible) to get the correct values.



 For example:



 animation-timing-function is not linear.animation-direction is not normal.multiple values in animation-name with different animation-duration‚Äôs and animation-delay‚Äôs.



